Imported Fuel to Boost India Nuclear Power by 35%, Standard Says

-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 
2011-03-08T05:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/imported-fuel-to-boost-india-nuclear-power-by-35-standard-says.html
Imported uranium will help  India 
generate 35 percent more nuclear power in the year ending March
31, Business Standard  reported , citing Shreyans Kumar Jain,
chairman of Nuclear Power Corp.  Uranium supply contracts with Russia, Kazakhstan and France
will help India increase nuclear generation to 25.5 billion
kilowatt-hours this financial year, the report said. India has
received 300 metric tons of the atomic fuel from France’s  Areva
SA (CEI) , it said.  Nuclear Power Corp., India’s monopoly atomic generator,
expects profit for the year to increase to 10 billion rupees
($222 million) from 4.16 billion rupees a year earlier, the
report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Archana Chaudhary in New Delhi at 
 achaudhary2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Foxwell at   sfoxwell@bloomberg.net . 